# Karpathy Principles

- Think before coding. State assumptions, surface tradeoffs, and ask when requirements are ambiguous.
- Simplicity first. Do the smallest thing that solves the real request; avoid speculative abstractions.
- Surgical changes. Touch only files needed for the task; do not rewrite nearby code just because it could be cleaner.
- Goal-driven execution. Define verifiable success criteria, then loop through focused checks until they pass.
